			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Dranik Scar 46-54, a good spot<a name="68688"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 2:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My experience in this spot is 3/4 boxing a 46-52 group, duoing a 52 bard/52 cleric and in a full group. This is, so far, my favorite spot cash/exp/safety wise, in the zone.
<br />

<br />
Location: From the PoD zone-in go south to the zone wall and follow it west, you will go through a little pass and see a rock midway up the zone wall. You are not far from the rune-turn in guy, and a little further from the sw zone corner. There is a little flatter bump in the zone wall by this rock. This is a good place to pull to and fight. (you could also chant kite around this rock, if you don't mind doing it on a hillside).
<br />

<br />
Nothing paths by this rock. Park the casters on top of it.
<br />

<br />
A little valley pans out in front of you with the possiblility of 3 nameds. There is a static named murkglider against the nearest building to the NW. Typically level 53 (52-54) with a ton of hp. Slowed he is pretty doable, but its a long fight. He drops a decent level 22 helm-common and a decent procing piercer, less common. There is a roving named Kyv that I have only seen drop a mediocre caster's wand. There is a roving 'Newbor' murkglider that drops a +10 atk neck, common and the Improved damage III cape, a little less common. 
<br />

<br />
The named murkgliders, at least, frequently can summon, even tho db con to a 52.
<br />

<br />
Dragorns---slow easy prey, either the commoner or the peon, but peon may stun you.
<br />

<br />
Noc's--hit harder, less hp than dragorns, the ones with longer names are more dangerous and backstabs are possible.
<br />

<br />
Kyv's--fast, can but rarely fire arrows at a distance, lower hit points and the longer named ones can string together a seriers of hits that can take a 3800 hp bard from 30% to zero in half the time it takes to cheal (trust me).
<br />

<br />
Ukons--cast a snare which can be invconvenient, and hit hard..but not a lot of hp. Again...longer name = meaner.
<br />

<br />
Rats--typical rats...I haven't noticed a poison disease problem from them (noc's/kyv/murks and I think Ukun will frequently drop a short duration posion).
<br />

<br />
All these are potential charms for charm fighting.
<br />

<br />
Murkgliders, tough, more hps...especially the spawns in this valley. Usually not charmable. The ones in the little building down low north of the corner are much easier than the ones that are static, or roam in the valley.
<br />

<br />
Possible drops:
<br />

<br />
Attunable augs (rare)
<br />

<br />
Discordant crystals (pricing on my server from 500 to 2k--used with discordant scrolls for turn-in to PoD's for porter spells.
<br />

<br />
Damaged magnetic bracer--4k plus on my server.
<br />

<br />
Lots of gems up to ruby. Hides, tusks various vendor loot cash drops typically better than old world drops in comparable zones.
<br />

<br />
You'll just have to research the bazaar on other items. There are some that have worth above vendor loot as turn-ins. (and some with huge bazaar prices on my server that are actually vendor loot only.)
<br />

<br />
There is no zone out near, PoD port out takes a while and training the zone-in probably won't work, and will sully your name. You could run to NC if you were careful. but thats in the nw corner.
<br />

<br />
Invis works well for travel, as does running high up on the zone walls.
<br />

<br />
If you are killing fast and the sw corner is open, go along the zone wall and pull from there as well rather than going north deeper (past the creek) to avoid adds.
<br />

<br />
Past 54 lots of lb's suggests moving on unless the farming aspect is too lucrative to give up.
<br />

<br />
Thats off the top of my head, please post any questions/corrections.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
